# 01_Wazuh_Setup
**Project:** Wazuh SIEM All-in-One Deployment (Ubuntu VM / Docker Compose)  
**Objective:** Deploy Wazuh Manager, Indexer, and Dashboard on Ubuntu and verify agent communication.

---

## Overview
This folder documents the complete steps taken to deploy Wazuh using Docker Compose on an Ubuntu Server VM (VMware). It includes installation commands, configuration changes, and verification steps. Screenshots of the running dashboard and registered agent(s) are included in `/screenshots`.

---

## System / VM Specs (example)
- Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS
- Memory: 8 GB (recommended)
- CPU: 2 vCPU
- Disk: 40 GB
- Network: NAT / Host-only (all lab VMs on same network)

---

## Quick install steps (copy-paste)

```bash
# update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# essentials
sudo apt install -y curl apt-transport-https ca-certificates gnupg lsb-release

# install docker
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg
echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] \
  https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io

# install docker compose plugin (or use legacy binary)
sudo apt install -y docker-compose-plugin

# prepare folder and download Wazuh compose file
mkdir -p ~/wazuh-docker && cd ~/wazuh-docker
curl -LO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.9/docker-compose.yml

# start Wazuh stack
docker compose up -d
# check status
docker compose ps
